annotation.TEXT: Okay, those koopas are just passing through, so I figured I'd be courteous and get out of their way.
"Fox, get this guy off me!"
Alright, it's... not boss time yet? Actually, it shouldn't be boss time yet since that wasn't a boss door.
Ow, my foot!
Gotta bullet hop onto the turn block bridge here.
Oh, man. Now this part is a bit tricky.
Maybe spin jumping here was a bad idea?
Okay, here, I believe you have to reveal a vine to remove the directional tiles, because you need these bullets to continue flying straight.
And, there you go. These 7 levels await your votes, which will determine where I go next time!
Oh, sure. I'll take an extra cape.
Huh. There was a certain rhythm to those blocks I just broke through that reminded me of the Goron dancing minigame from one of the Zelda Oracle games for Game Boy Color.

Bam! Take that, Hammer Brother! (Good thing my aim was accurate there!)
Huh. I wonder if there's stuff over to the right...
Alright, now it's boss time!
Just making sure I didn't jump over anything important back there.
Alright, all of the important bullets appeared for me, thankfully!
Oh, come on. Get up there... Oh, wait. That's right. I've gotta bullet hop, since that seems to be the theme of the level now.
Hmm... How am I supposed to make this jump?
There's a springboard. I wonder what I'll need it for...
Oh, that's neat. The blue shell and disco shell took each other out. And here I was thinking for a second that I'd have to deal with them both myself!
It's rather obvious how one could farm lives here.
Whoa, man! Thank you, Bullet Bill! (I'm surprised I missed that simple jump, and even more surprised that a bullet happened to be in the right place to save me!)

Hmm... I wonder if it was a good idea to hit that upper block. Well, at least I now know that the lower block must also just hold one coin, since they started in the same X position, so there's no need to be insane enough to check that one!
Ah, there's our resident wizard.

Hi! Welcome Back! Voting results now!
Piece of cake.
Nah, I'm good. Let me just do a quick double-check back there...
Hmm... I don't think I'm going to annotate in the number of 40-star goal tape hits or number of videos where I play multiple bonus games.

Hmm... I could possibly turn this into a 1♥P combo, but I don't want to take a risk right now.
Alright, so up next is the other first place vote, 6-3.

I guess the wizard is taking a break now.
Yeah, it was rather obvious that that would be a vine. (Well, it could've potentially been a P-switch as well.)

Whoa, geez! What makes this trickier is that the hitbox for a block sprite is a bit wider than the hitbox for a block object, so I have to jump around a block sprite at a wider angle than with a block object to avoid hitting my head on it.
Ow, my butt!
There wouldn't happen to be a replacement power up in one of these blocks, would there?
Some bony enemies, and... that's it. Okay.
Oh, man! It's 8-A all over again! Actually, this appears to be much easier, and there's nothing to the left that I have to worry about.
Thank you, cape!
Yay, I opened up a tiny shortcut path here! Now I don't have to go the very slightly longer way around if I want to go from the W7 warp star to the W6 warp star here or vice versa!
Alright, let's see what that pipe skipped over.
I can get an extra cape over here, and... Wow, really? You know what? Now I'm going to want to revisit this level after I clear it just to check something!
Okay, I remember how this part gave raocow headaches. Hmm... Maybe I can despawn the shell by screen scrolling?
To be continued...
So, that means I'm heading to 9-7 next!
Whoa. It might not be a good idea to spin jump there.
Whoa, that could've gotten hairy if I had let more bullets be fired there.
Bonus game average so far: 217 / 30 = 7.233 1♥Ps each.
And the winner is yellow!
And here we have diagonal directional arrows for the Bullet Bills to change directions with. These are pretty neat.
Alright. Now, there's hopefully a replacement power up in one of those ? blocks back over here, assuming I don't let the wizard screw me over...
Yep! You can practically skip the whole level by just jumping to the right of that exit pipe! Wow, this would be great for speedrunners that are going for 100% exits and don't care about star coins!
Yep, I'd say the goal was near. Well, that was a pretty neat level. As the level went on, it tended to focus on the bullets much more than the slippery slopes, but that's okay.
So, I guess the requirement for reaching midpoint this time is that you need to bring the springboard with you.
Blue shell = 6-3. Yellow Shell = 9-7.
No, not that Slippy! (Voice clip taken from Star Fox 64, of course.)

...You know, I should've checked that reset pipe before I went through the effort of building that bridge the first time...

Alright this time I'm using the Ievan Polkka song from ASMT that 8azaz22 gave me a link to (Thanks!), and I've included this link in the description. Oh, and the blue shell is 6-3 and the yellow shell is 9-7.

Hmm... I don't think I'll be checking every block here, but if one of them contains something good that I missed, let me know!
